    "description": {
      "value": "<blockquote data-start=\"1036\" data-end=\"1450\"><p data-start=\"1038\" data-end=\"1061\"><strong data-start=\"1038\" data-end=\"1059\">Auspice: Galliard</strong></p><p data-start=\"1068\" data-end=\"1264\">Galliards are the storytellers, singers, and emotional heart of the Garou. They preserve history through song and legend, inspire allies through performance, and remind the Nation why it fights.</p><p data-start=\"1271\" data-end=\"1450\">A Galliard commands attention when recounting Garou history, performing ritual songs, or rallying others through art, speech, or passion. Even in defeat, their words carry weight.</p></blockquote><p><strong data-start=\"2128\" data-end=\"2152\">Voice of the Nation.</strong><br data-start=\"2152\" data-end=\"2155\" />When you perform, recount Garou history, or rally others through art or speech, elders and spirits recognize your role as a Galliard. You are expected to speak at moots and gatherings, and your words carry cultural authority among the Garou.</p><p data-start=\"1452\" data-end=\"1537\"></p>",
